methods.name: public boolean isFullTracking()
methods.comment:
* Represents whether to enable full GNSS tracking. * *

If true, GNSS chipset switches off duty cycling. In such a mode, no clock * discontinuities are expected, and when supported, carrier phase should be continuous in * good signal conditions. All non-denylisted, healthy constellations, satellites and * frequency bands that the chipset supports must be reported in this mode. The GNSS chipset * is allowed to consume more power in this mode. If false, GNSS chipset optimizes power via * duty cycling, constellations and frequency limits, etc. * *

Full GNSS tracking mode affects GnssMeasurement and other GNSS functionalities * including GNSS location.
